nix has been fixed.  What changed

 Core fix — src/libexpr/primops/wasm.cc (4 lines changed):
 The catch (Error & e) block in prim_wasm was re-throwing a base
 nix::Error, which tryEval ignores. Changed it to throw ThrownError
 (subclass of AssertionError, which is what tryEval catches):

 ```cpp
   // Before:
   catch (Error & e) {
       e.addTrace(state.positions[pos], "while executing...");
       throw;
   }

   // After:
   catch (Error & e) {
       state.error<ThrownError>("%s", Uncolored(e.message()))
           .atPos(pos)
           .withTrace(pos, fmt("while executing the Wasm function
 from '%s'", wasmPath))
           .debugThrow();
   }
 ```

 Test fixtures — two new WASM modules:
 - pure_panic.wasm — non-WASI, calls host panic function
 - wasi_panic.wasm — WASI, calls host panic function

 Test cases — 4 new tests in wasm.sh:
 - tryEval catches non-WASI WASM panic
 - tryEval catches WASI WASM panic
 - Panic error message is preserved in output
 - Normal calls still work after panic tests

 Results: 38/38 onix-modules eval tests pass (was 36/38). update flake input references
